author: maxb
msg: * subversion/bindings/swig/svn_delta.i: I haven't the foggiest idea what
"Cancel the typemap as they aren't returned valued
in member functions if editor."
means, but since the only effect of deleting the associated code appears to
be that svn_ra_replay() then gets its editor argument wrapped for Perl,
I'm going to do just that, and delete it.

author: maxb
msg: * subversion/bindings/swig/svn_ra.i: General re-ordering and comment cleanup.

author: malcolm
msg: Remove conditional support for zlib, since zlib is now required.
* configure.in
Don't set SVN_HAVE_ZLIB.
* subversion/libsvn_subr/stream.c
Remove checks for SVN_HAVE_ZLIB, and code conditional on !SVN_HAVE_ZLIB.
* subversion/include/svn_io.h
(svn_stream_compressed): Note that compression support is always
available in Subversion 1.4 and later.

author: malcolm
msg: Treat zlib more like other libraries by linking to it only where required,
rather than unconditionally adding it to every link line.
* Makefile.in
(SVN_ZLIB_LIBS): New.
* build.conf
(libsvn_subr): Add a missing dependency on zlib.
(zlib): Add 'external-lib', so that non-win32 build targets will link
to SVN_ZLIB_LIBS when dependent upon zlib.
* configure.in
Add the zlib library to SVN_ZLIB_LIBS instead of to LIBS.

author: maxb
msg: SWIG: Consolidate 'const char **OUTPUT' application, no functional change to
wrappers.
[in subversion/bindings/swig/]
* include/svn_string.swg: Consolidate applications here.
* core.i, svn_client.i, svn_fs.i, svn_ra.i, svn_wc.i: Remove applications.
